In [5]:
#   , 
#        
aws = utils.AWSUtils()
try:
    conn = aws.connect_to_db()
    cell_data = pd.read_sql(
        'SELECT \
            t.passenger_count_total, \
            t.average_trip_ph, \
            r.region_id, \
            r.west, \
            r.east, \
            r.south, \
            r.north \
        FROM \
            (SELECT \
                sum(ad.passenger_count_sum) as passenger_count_total, \
                sum(ad.passenger_count_sum/ad.passenger_count_mean)/24/31 as average_trip_ph, \
                ad.pickup_region_id \
            FROM \
                mldb.taxi_aggregateddata ad \
            WHERE \
                MONTH(ad.pickup_datetime) = 5 \
                AND YEAR(ad.pickup_datetime) = 2016 \
            GROUP BY \
                ad.pickup_region_id \
            ) t \
        RIGHT JOIN mldb.taxi_regions r ON r.region_id=t.pickup_region_id;',
        conn
    )
finally:
    conn.close()

).to_crs(epsg=3857)

#   --
esb_location = geopandas.tools.geocode('Empire State Building').to_crs(epsg=3857)
x, y = esb_location.geometry.x[0], esb_location.geometry.y[0]
ax.scatter(x, y, color='red')
ax.annotate('Empire State Building', (x, y), va='bottom', fontsize=10)

#  
ctx.add_basemap(ax, zoom=12)
ax.set_axis_off()

#  
geo_cell_data = geopandas.GeoDataFrame(
    cell_data[['passenger_count_total', 'average_trip_ph']].fillna(0),
    geometry=[
        Polygon([
            (w, n), 
            (e, n), 
            (e, s), 
            (w, s), 
            (w, n)
        ]) for w, e, s, n in zip(
            cell_data.west, 
            cell_data.east, 
            cell_data.south, 
            cell_data.north
        )
    ],
    crs={'init': 'epsg:4326'}
)

colorscale = branca.colormap.StepColormap(
    ['white', 'lightblue', 'lightgreen', 'yellow', 'orange', 'red', 'purple'],
    index=[0, 1, 10, 50, 100, 200, 500],  
    vmin=0, 
    vmax=geo_cell_data.average_trip_ph.max()
)

#  
folium.GeoJson(
    geo_cell_data,
    name='Average taxi trip per hour',
    style_function=lambda feature: {
        'fillOpacity': 0.7,
        'weight': 0,
        'fillColor': colorscale(feature['properties']['average_trip_ph'])
    }
).add_to(interactive_map)

#  
interactive_map
